0.content:
With a throat the colour of the koel, shining with celestial radiance and bearing lotus-marks on both feet; adorned and resplendent in yellow garments, with lotus-like eyes, ever gently smiling; in his hands the bow and arrows, attended by his monkey-companions; I bow to Janaki’s lord, Raghava Rama—ever compassionate, Rama garlanded with flowers. ॥1॥

Those two lotus-like feet, the glory of the Kosala-king’s throne, tender and lovely, venerated even by Maheshvara; Janaki’s hands, red as lotus-petals, draw the contemplative mind like bees to a blossom. ॥2॥

Fair as jasmine and moonlight, beautiful—husband of Ambikā, fulfiller of desires; I salute Śaṅkara whose compassionate, lotus-like eyes liberate from the bondage of desire. ॥3॥
